definition: to be a newcomer/just off the boat

sentences.english: I was new in New York one time, too.
sentences.chinese: 我也曾是一个初来乍到纽约的人。

sentences.english: There are many things that as a stranger initially threw me for a loop.
sentences.chinese: 最初，有很多事让我这个初来乍到的异乡人眩晕。

sentences.english: In its recent approach to Africa, China could not be more different from the West.
sentences.chinese: 初来乍到非洲，中国与西方国家的行事方式截然不同。

sentences.english: U.S. companies are relatively new to the Indian defense market.
sentences.chinese: 美国公司对于印度国防市场相对来说是初来乍到。
